# Zhemchug, Republic of Buryatia

}}
Zhemchug (; , Jemheg) is a rural locality (a selo) in Tunkinsky District, Republic of Buryatia, Russia. The population was 1,138 as of 2010. There are 16 streets.
Geography
Zhemchug is located 24&nbsp;km east of Kyren (the district's administrative centre) by road. Okhor-Shibir is the nearest rural locality.
